sec.p:
Amendments are changes made to the research after a favorable opinion by the accredited IRB has been given. All substantial amendments will be notified to the IRB, as they requires IRB approval, and to the competent authority. A “substantial amendment” is defined as an amendment to the terms of the IRB application, or to the protocol or any other supporting documentation, that is likely to affect to a significant degree:
The safety or physical or mental integrity of the patients of the trial;
The scientific value of the trial;
The conduct or management of the trial;
The quality or safety of any intervention used in the trial; and
The addition of a new experimental compound.
